  <bioghist id="aspace_a44e165535424540376652082cc1891a">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Burnham Kelly was Dean of the College of Architecture, Art and Planning, 1960-1971.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_67f6cc2788c2644c96410c564d6d3bda">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Correspondence, manuscripts, and reports relating to the development of an architecture and regional planning program at the University of Puerto Rico and to Kelly's visit to observe the planning and architecture programs at the University Del Valle in Colombia; file on the planning of a Cornell art museum, 1959-1968; report of the Centennial Planning Committee, 1960-1961, including material on the size of the University. Also, bibliographic cards on construction techniques.</p><p> Additional records include speeches, lesson plans, consulting project and subject files, concerning Burnham Kelly's career as Dean of the College of Architecture, Art and Planning, 1960-1971.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_af02e57116d7d5b4f980d8717bf804e5">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Burnham Kelly Papers, #15-1-1633. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
